Quality steel

These bits and the whole screwdriver system in a whole are superior products.

J
Julius Martin
Great product, missing opportunities

I love the screw driver! It actuallu makes the tedious task of driving screws kind of fun. I've bought along with the standard screwdriver and heads, a few extra bit sets.

After this purchase, I realized that I had no where to put the bits. An intuitive bit holder for LTT bits would be an awesome side product!

Another issue I faced was the length of the drivers are quite short. This makes it hard to reach screws in electronics that are enclosed deep within the mechanism. An extension piece for the screwdriver would make this product absolutely perfect!

All that said, this is the best screwdriver I've ever used.

Love the bit selection super useful for my computer builds and house fixin!

General screwdriver use

The bits work well enough, I wish they sold all the bits together for a dollar off or something in that nature. As I bought all of them.

I had to find JIS bits for use on my Honda/Subaru on McMaster. Perhaps something that Linus can add.

P
Paul Walters
Solid Screwdriver Bits

There honestly isn't too much to say about these, they are good quality bits that do their job well and fit in the LTT Screwdriver. The pre-made packs are affordable and well thought out as is the minimal packaging they come in.

In regards to a storage suggestion though...

It would be interesting if LTT could offer something similar to those "customizable" driver bit trays you see at the hardware store from the likes of DeWalt, Bosch, Milwaukee, etc. They tend to be all a similar generic latching plastic box with "swappable" inserts... but you can't buy the inserts separately! I'd honestly pay for a version that you could customize and upgrade; you could even sell them "pre-loaded" with customer selected bit packs!

Just a thought.

T
Terry Wright

Screwdriver Bit Set

M
Mitchell
So nice I bought it twice!

I enjoyed mine so much that I bought this second one for my dad. Both get used all the time and put my other ratcheting screwdrivers to shame.

Q
Quincy
Decent, but brittle

I ordered all of the bit sets, together with the screwdriver, a few months ago.
All bits look great and look like they're great quality.

However.. This happened to not be the case for me, since I've had to - twice now - request new sets. 1 bit of both the Specialty set and the Torx/Security set bent and broke during use.
I have some experience when it comes to repairing phones, laptops and whatnot, so I know how to handle precision bits. I used to use a cheap set until I decided to treat myself to this LTT merch.

The cheaper bits never even had a scratch, while on 2 separate occasions the LTT bits broke. I hope these incidents were flukes, but I somehow doubt that.

I hope the new sets received (for free, with good and friendly service) prove these to be flukes, since I really like these products.

If so, I will update my review accordingly.

Be cautious.

But the packaging and delivery...\u003c/b\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eGood product. Stable and feels like good quality. Great design on the packaging but lazily made. Good, but not great

Before get into review, Iâ€™d recommend this screwdriver all day ,one, even w/ the minor 2 issues it has.
Hated to delete 2 stars for the following, but have to be fair and as dint have Â½ starsâ€¦.no choice. For comparison, Milwaukee (a fav brand and Klein; had 1 and 0 stars respectively for the ratcheting screwdrivers b/c of slop, storage breakage of Klein, and hardbjt removal on Milwaukee to name just a few that I reviewed after 4 mins this of use)
1) would prefer the silver color for bits just like the silver shaft, as the black is wearing right off and quickly
2) the size/number of bit is pretty much impossible to read w/ the black coating, not to mention, black coating wearing off and makes it harder. If Bit No/size a black 9r same color of the silver shaft, would be so much easier to read; & for those not in construction trades and donâ€™t know bit size by site, Ames it quite difficult to read. So much so, Iâ€™ve got 4 ppl on my crew pulling out cell camera to zoom in to see what bit size they have; especially for the ones not used dailyâ€¦.like specially, torx, hex, Phillips bit sets that can go down to â€œ0-00â€ zies etcâ€¦
Lastly, having the black coating flake off into sensitive electronics can be bad; but Iâ€™ve yet to have had an issue personally from this, and hope never will.
As I like the black, especially when receiving my multiple black shaft â€˜drivers, gonna look pretty awesome! Making my total number of screwdrivers to 5 And total bit packs to 19 total, yep, thatâ€™s right; cuz when in electronics repair and definitely the trades (a sparky, GC, remodeled, & doing a lot of hardware installsâ€¦can wear thru bits quite fast, depending on use case). If the color and stamped â€œbit size/numberâ€ being an issueâ€¦.5/5 all day long, and do like the fit, magnet, & storage in handle more than any of my other 40 screwdrivers. Lastly, the ratchet selector mechanism is actually CORRECT and not backwards from all others, so thx Linus for pushing this feature! Otherwise, balance great, bits so easy to remove/replace in storage handle and use! My fav screwdriver to date and definitely my fav ratcheting screwdriver period! Nothing comes close for price, features, functions, AND USING.
Now Iâ€™m just waiting for that Srubby, and be happy to test for you, cuz having a stubby for hvac/plumbing/electrical, cabinet installsâ€¦.are very valuable, imo.

J
J.W.
Great screwdriver, no torx feels bad

I like the screwdriver a lot, it's exactly as advertised and works great.

However, I feel like torx screws are way more common than square ones, I would have liked to have at least some torx bits included, and it feels like a cheap upsell to not have any in there. Also, two flatheads are too much, you could have easily done no squares, single flathead, and you could add three torx bits, instead we get three (maybe four) useless bits.

Peter Broad
Bits Galore and great service

I purchased the LTT screwdriver; which is amazingly useful; and one of the straight bits was pointed rather than straight. LTT replaced the entire standard set of bits and offered me a second set as well.
I love all the bits and I use the screwdriver around the house all the time. It is my go-to screwdriver. I have all the bit sets now so I am hoping Linus is working on a bit holder.
Great customer support and great product.

E.S.
what am amazing tool!

When you guys announced the driver I was so jazzed to get my hands on it. Watching how much effort went into the design,the materials and testing. If this thing was on the same level as the 3! Dad hats I've purchased over the last 3 years, I knew I was in for a great experience. This driver does not disappoint, love the handle design, big fan of the bit storage, and the ratcheting action and magnet make every job easier! I was an employee of Home Depot for 15 years and in all that time, every driver I've had in hand can't hold a candle to the LTT driver. You all have achieved insane quality without gouging your customers ala Snap-on or other big brands. Only question I have is there would be plans to do a "game bit" for working on Super Nintendo and such?

This has been on my hip for 40 hours a week at my job ever since I got this screwdriver, and its yet to let me down. The one thing I don't have is a great place to store all the specialty bits I also ordered. I'm not going to be able to keep them in the LTT cardboard forever every time I have to swap out my bit loadouts. I might have to 3D print a holder for all my lesser used security bits.

Good... BUT

Bought 2 sets of the Metric Hex Set and 2 sets off the Torx / Security Torx Set. The Torx set is good from what I have used of it so far, so I would recommend them.

The Metric Hex is a different story. While I canâ€™t fault the bits themselves the issue is with myself.

I didnâ€™t read what was actually in the bit set. Whilst you do get 12 bits in the box you actually only get 9 different bits. I stupidly thought I was getting 12 different sized bits because why would you sell a bit set with 3 duplicate bit sizes? If I had off seen that I wouldnâ€™t never have bought them.

Overall - Good... but double check before you buy.

However I'm missing pz1 and pz2 bits a lot, since I'm more of a hobbyist than pc builder, and in Europe the PZ bits are more widely used than PH.

J
Jason Bent
JIS Bits?

Hey Linus, you've said on the WAN show several times that you read every review so I figured this may be the best place to make this request. Would you please look into adding JIS (Japanese Industrial Standard) bits to the options for the screwdriver? On all Japanese motorcycles (and presumably cars as well?) the cross head screws and bolts that appear to be phillips are NOT that, but rather they are JIS. They look very similar, but trying to use a standard phillips driver on a JIS fastener very often results in the fastener stripping out and having to then be drilled out. As a mechanic, having the proper tool makes a big difference and I would love to make your already kickass screwdriver an even more versatile tool in my toolbox. I know I may be in the minority as it's mostly tech enthusiasts who are buying this tool, but I've been shilling it to all my fellow mechanics as it is already a well built driver that stands up to real world abuse in a mechanic shop. Thanks for hearing me out and congrats on your much deserved success!

R.D.
Needs to be a Bundle with Storage

The bits are fine on their own. My biggest complaint about the LTT Screwdriver is its lack of storage. I want there to be a way to properly store all the bits when not in the handle of the screwdriver. Think something like the bit storage with iFixit kits. There could be one with a slot to set down the driver along with all the bits, or another option would be a small box that just manages all the bits.

Almost tempted to knock it down to two stars because of the bits packaging in general. Iâ€™m glad itâ€™s just a thick card stock kind of stuff, but nearly all of the boxes tore the first time I opened them. The ones that didnâ€™t I had to be super careful not to let them tear, however theyâ€™re all torn now. Bits flying everywhere! Itâ€™s madness I tell you! Madness!

I donâ€™t have a problem with this being the basic option for people who are getting replacements or just want to toss the spares in a drawer. I would just rather have a place for them to all live that wonâ€™t cause them to get mixed up or lost. I realize it would cost more money, but Iâ€™m willing to buy a full set of bits again if it means Iâ€™d get a nice box to store them when theyâ€™re not in the driver.

The bits are bits. They do their job well, theyâ€™d get five stars if there was better storage for them.

Y
Yuri N.
Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder

Still waiting on my screwdriver (ordered bits first), quality seems nice but donâ€™t fit in any of my existing drivers to test properly. Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder. The cardboard box they came in is already torn just from shipping and the bits are just flopping around inside.

It would be nice if there was a screwdriver accessory to hold spare bits, either a dedicated box with little clips to hold them in place. Or, if you wanted to be fancy the holder could be a little pod with the same internals as the screwdriver! I think that would be cool!

D
D.H.
Love the bits. Hate the holders.

I haven't had a chance to use any yet but the finish is perfect, hollow ground on the flats and no burs to be found.
The packs themselves are very hard to open without tearing the card stock construction, there is nothing retaining the bits inside and WHEN the holder finally tears you'll just have to store them loose or buy and modify a cheap 3rd party holder to fit the smaller bit shanks.

Tip for opening these packs: slide a small blade like a dinner knife or feeler gauge in from the side and twist it back towards the hinge to pry the tab up. It'll help the holder last as long as possible and you're less likely to dump the bits.

A

Just the tip?

You bet it's just the tip, multiple black ones at that!

Jokes aside, these are very high quality. LTT just needs to make a lil bit case for these short babies, because once you remove a single bit from the original packaging it's like the Berlin wall collapsed with the rest.

R
Richard Lum

always handy to have all the bibs and bobs

M
M.M.
Poor packaging resulted in many missing bits on delivery

Now, I get that we all strive to be "eco" this and "bio" that, but this item is packaged straight-up wrong.
Only 7/12 bits arrived safe, the rest are lost - the bigger box that my shipment arrived in was "sealed", but not "hermetically sealed". Actually, that's another thing... why isn't either of the boxes even properly sealed with scotch tape? How does such a rookie mistake even happen?

Take note: the bits are *only* packaged in a tiny cardboard box. This box is not sealed in any way - no plastic, no glue, no "tiny IKEA-style rubber bit-holding-thingy".
It can just open itself up while in transit - in fact, it seems like a dead certainty.

LTT Guys, I love you, I love your eco-efforts, but at some point reality steps in. If Linus reviewed a competitor and *barely half the bits were even in the box*... well...

C
Cameron

\u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eEvery LTT video interrupted by \"get screwdriver', sometimes 2 or 3 times.  So I did.  I actually got 2.  figured a good Christmas present for my friend.   The order was confirmed with 2-6 day delivery   That was on August 21st last year.  I e-mailed and was told there was a wait that I agreed to do when I signed up.  And still, I watch the ads for this great screwdriver on the videos.  On Dec. 24th I got an e-mail saying 'shipment data received' and here we are.  The bits seem great.  Unfortunately I've been waiting for something to put them in since Summer.  Keep this in mind next time you see the smarmy reviews about how long wish takes, or how crowd sourced projects end up taking months (years?) longer than they were promised. \u003cb class='jdgm-rev__title'\u003eGreat, But No iPhone Standoff Bit.\u003c/b\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eEvery iPhone since the 5 (almost a decade) has used the same standoffs to hold the logic board down.  I purchased four of the screwdrivers with specialty bit addons for the whole team in our repair shop.  My hope was to replace all of the cheap bits/screwdrivers we have in house, especially the y000/0.6 that never seem to fit right.  I thought these would have all the specialty bits I would need for a small repair shop, but as I replaced all the commonly used iFixit bits in my silicone mat with these I realized that the iPhone standoff bit I use almost daily was not a part of the specialty bit set (or any offered here).  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHear my pleas and please offer this as an optional bit in this set or another because I discovered finding a 1/4\" iPhone standoff bit online is basically impossible.  It would have to be custom ordered/made in bulk.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__pics'\u003e  \u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__vids'\u003e   \u003c/div\u003e Love it

The screwdriver is very well made, the tolerances are perfect, the ratchet action is really nice and tight. If Linus reads this review, I would like to suggest that the extra bit sets be sold in a combo pack with a case with an all-black or black and orange option with a black or stainless metal clasp, also put a hole on it that's big enough to put a carabiner through it.

D
Daniel
The Bit heads are sometimes not large enough

I used all of the extra bit heads that I ordered to build PCs/ 3D printer/cat house/moar stuff. The largest hex bit head was often not big enough besides that one downfall. The bits are durable and I liked them.

Just the Bits You Need ;) (standard set)

The bits look fine.
The packaging could use some improvement.
The stamping on the bits should get a lot of improvement.
Overall I love them and I will be restocking some of the other variants too.

It's screwdriver bits, for the LTT screwdriver. Pretty simple! The specific ones I needed for my old gameboy worked perfectly.

Bits no driver.

D
David Rhodes
Don't know yet, haven't gotten the screw driver lol

Have all the bits, but waiting for the driver. I'm sure it'll be good with all the care ltt put into it

T
Tim
Great bits, but packaging needs some adjustments.

I bought 9 sets of bits, about 3 of them arrived in tact, 2 were partially in tact, and 4 had come open during shipping and were scattered throughout the package.

Not the worst thing ever, but unfortunately it seems one of those loose bits exfilrated the package during shipping, so one set isn't complete.

I'd like to see some tape or a sticker placed over the bit packet opening to ensure they stay closed until opened with a knife or scissors.

As a secondary product, it'd be great if you stocked a large, labelled bit-holder tray to store all the bits which aren't currently equipped in the screwdriver.

As for the bits themselves, they look excellent.
Great work on the actual product!

A
Anonymous
Scattered Bits, but overall (just) ok

All bits arrived, but they arrived scattered around the main packaging. I appreciate LTT trying to reduce plastic use and keeping packaging somewhat minimal, but they need to figure out something to keep the bits in the package so the bits don't end up scattered around the main package.

Apart from that, my next biggest complaint is some of the bits are very difficult to read the embossed text, and I would have loved for the embossed text to be on all 6 sides. It seems some screws aren't embossed as deeply as others. When loading out the screwdriver, I like to have the embossed text visible so I can better find the bit I am looking for, but some of the bits are really difficult to tell. I group similar bits together so I can use the near by bits to determine what a particular bit is, but would like to not have to.

For Storage, I have the set that came with the screwdriver and 1 other load out. I keep 1 set in the screwdriver and the other bits in the original package and keep the package in the box the Screwdriver shipped in.

All the bits seem very durable, so overall I would rate the bits as just ok.

I
Invvard
Good bits but it lacks a holder

These are good bits (as good as the ones that come with the Screwdriver), the only grief is that it comes in a thin cardboard holder and there is no way it'll hold anything in after a few open/close. Even being cautious opening it for the first time didn't prevent some tear in the cardboard.

I don't think LTT Store could offer a holder for the price, but something should be offered, i.e. a rubber holder along with an optional case that could hold said rubber holders. I'm pretty sure the team is already thinking about something, let's hope it won't take them 3 years to come up with a solution, hahaha

In the mean time, there are some options available on Amazon for example, but they are for standard sized bits. It works but it requires some effort to extract the bits as there is very little going above the edge.

On a final note, I would have appreciated some visual(s) of the packaging.

{"html":"
R
Roar
Needs a case

Maybe I am wrong, maybe I am being too critical, but I am so surprised that these bit sets do not come with a case/holder.

Every bits set I have bought in my entire life came with a case/holder, so I naturally thought it would be the same here.

I am giving it a one star due to feedback and the lack of adjustment in the product page. There should be images of the *actual products*, actual showing that it comes in a cardbox box where the bits are just stacked horisontally next to each other. For me this is close to false advertisement because a lot of people clearly expected more from this product.

I don't care if the product would be a bit more expensive, just give me a friggin' case to store them with. I bought the screwdriver and three additional bits sets in order to be organized when building PCs, but now I have to find a way to organize the stuff so I can avoid losing them. My experience is ruined because it feels cheap. The product is great, but not the whole experience.

J
Jonathan Huff
Great price for a great variety of bits! I love that I can fit all 12 in the LTT screwdriver handle

My only real feedback is that I'd like to have a nice place to store and organize all my bits, since I bought every one of the sets!

J
John Hoffman
Its nearly a replacement for my old iFixit kit

I kind of love these bits. The quality seems excellent, and the variety is equally good. The overall selection is almost a superset of my old iFixit kit.

I even designed and 3d printed a holder for them all. :)

V
Valentin L.
Almost great

I bought each set to go with my LTT screwdriver. I'm happy with them but I have a couple of notes to make it perfect : black is pretty but hard to see the engraved size on it and I know it might be an European thing but why not a Pozidriv set, they are like everywhere here (I have a big ifixit set of bits, they got almost every bits you offer and little more like a complete set of Pozidriv).

For people saying they need a holder, I know you guys are working on it, but I really love Wera design on their â€05136463001 and â€05136459001 products, it's simple and don't feel cheap, I'll use them for now and wait to see what you guys come up with.

N
Noah Wheeler
Bits are fine, lack of holders limits useability

The bits are fine. Not a huge fan of black as it makes it just a little extra difficult in poor lightning to tell which bit is which, but i'll give it a pass because it looks cool. That being said especially with the smaller sizes it becomes hard to tell.
already when putting a bit back into the packaging I can't tell if I've put it in the correct order or not.

What I don't like I really would've expected a little rubber/plastic bit holder or something other than cardboard to keep the bits in place and organized when they aren't in the screwdriver itself. I bought 2 additional bit sets and I don't really want to risk putting them in my tool bag because I know the cardboard is gonna pop out and a million tiny little black bits are going to get lost in the shadows. I'm giving such a harsh hit on the rating just because I believe that these lack of holders are really gonna limit the use I get out of it unless I go out and buy my own additional holder, something that I really shouldn't have to do. I can't remember the last time I bought a set of bits that didn't come with holders.

Finally just a small pet peeve that doesn't really matter because the cardboard packaging isn't going to last anyway is that I don't love that you can't tell what bit you are grabbing out of the box. The icon on the front of box when the flap is open just shows the base style. This means on the torx set 9/12 bits have an identical icon. A little text below each icon with the type of bit like you have on the other side of the flap would've been nice. This is probably a bit pedantic as we've already established the cardboard is going to get trashed anyway.

I'll update the review if I notice any functionality issues with the shorter design but so far seems like there's no major downsides. My primary application is generally automotive and random engineering projects.

T
Teagan Werner
High quality stuff

No corners weâ€™re cut. There more than enough to last a long timw

C
Chris
Torx Set

Bit quality is great.

Would have preferred the Torx set include T27 and T40 (maybe T35) rather than the smaller sizes. Understandable for a tech-focused product, but the smaller end of this set feels more at home in a precision driver kit, not a full size ratcheting driver.

Greatly appreciate the lack of single use plastic in the packaging, but would like to see a cardboard package that at least holds the bits in place. Just some little dividers so they don't float around freely when a couple are removed.

J
Jason Lavay

Screwdriver Bit Set

a
abnewwest
Fine I guess

The non-standard length, well, that's just silly and lacks imagination, kind of like selling bits in only a cardboard box rather than with a clip to hold them.

Torx pack skips size 27 security, one of the most common and no Pozidrive for the Europeans.

M
Matt Finnie
TORX FTW!

I don't know how many times I find I need a TORX bit for something and can't seem to ever find the right one. There are 12 of them in the TORX set ranging from T3 to T30! I shouldn't have any trouble getting the right one now and is a must in my toolbox. Combined with all the bits that come with the screwdriver I have a lot of great options should I need them. The only downside I see is that the bits come in a cardboard box so it's kind of useless to store them in it. I would have loved to have the option to buy a durable bit storage box to keep them in, and I may have even picked up some additional bit packages just in case. Overall great product and has a nice range of available bits, but the storage options could have been better.

C
Christopher Sanders
Buy multiples and safe yourself time

I purchased 1 of EACH bit set. Save yourself some time and just buy 1 of each NOW. FYI, when you buy these, go ahead and magnetic or rubberized bit holders on Amazon. The screwdriver comes with the "Standard" bit set but I would recommend buying a backup set as well.

Great, Butâ€¦..

The bits are great. However a bit holder for the additional bits would be great rather than storing them in the cardboard boxes that they ship in.

G
G.R.
good but not great IMO (Metric set review)

So I use a lot of the H2 (2mm) and H2.5 (2.5mm) for RC race cars and the bits are way too loose for me. I use MIP tools for RC and they are amazing, but uncomfortable, so when I bought the LTT screwdriver I was excited that it came with 2 and 2.5mm hex bits because I didn't doubt my boi Linus about the comfort. Unfortunately the Hexes are loose and the 2mm actually measured 1.95mm on my calipers and that is bad when it comes to small screws that need to be tight for competitive RC racing. the 2.5mm bit was 2.47 and 3mm was spot on and felt great. MIP tools use a flat sharp tip and these are more soft and rounded. Wouldn't recommend these if you need to remove some screws that have Loctite on them. screwdriver is amazing though. My boi Linus didn't lie when he said "trust me bro"

S
Stephen
Disappointing packaging

Love the screwdriver and the bits themselves are good. I bought 3 additional bit sets with my screwdriver and 2/3 of them were opened and the bits scattered through the shipping box rattling around loose. For how much Linus focuses on packaging of products he reviews I expected a lot more there tbh.

J
Joshua
All the bits...

I ended up buying all of the available bit packages, except for the standard bit set since th at already came with the screwdriver.

The bits seem good for the most part, though I do find some of the markings hard to read and a couple just don't seem to be there at all.

I would really love to have a labelled case for bit storage. While the box they come in has a nice presentation, it isn't really suitable for long term storage and doesn't hold the bits in place.

I have looked at generic options, but they generally aren't labelled and since these bits are a bit shorter than normal, they would be challenging to use. In the case of some magnetic options, they would go too far into the holder and be hard to identify / remove from the holder. In the more standard rubber strip designs, you I find they get inserted too far and have I have to use another bit to get the bit out.

Impressions on Day 1

So the loss of a star is because of the packaging. 2 of my bit boxes were opened and torn in the package and bits were loose. A small sticker on the opening tab should have prevented this and should be easy and low cost to add.
Besides shipping my first impressions are that these bits look and feel like good quality.
They're a consumable so your mileage will vary. Also 100% need a bit storage solution, I'll probably design and print my own, but not everyone has access to these sorts of tools, so purchasing one would be a nice option.
Excited to put these bad boys to use

\u003cb class='jdgm-rev__title'\u003eDecent 1st gen screwdriver\u003c/b\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eNot bad overall. Quality steel

These bits and the whole screwdriver system in a whole are superior products.

J
Julius Martin
Great product, missing opportunities

I love the screw driver! It actuallu makes the tedious task of driving screws kind of fun. I've bought along with the standard screwdriver and heads, a few extra bit sets.

After this purchase, I realized that I had no where to put the bits. An intuitive bit holder for LTT bits would be an awesome side product!

Another issue I faced was the length of the drivers are quite short. This makes it hard to reach screws in electronics that are enclosed deep within the mechanism. An extension piece for the screwdriver would make this product absolutely perfect!

All that said, this is the best screwdriver I've ever used.

A
Alexandro

Love the bit selection super useful for my computer builds and house fixin!

General screwdriver use

The bits work well enough, I wish they sold all the bits together for a dollar off or something in that nature. As I bought all of them.

I had to find JIS bits for use on my Honda/Subaru on McMaster. Perhaps something that Linus can add.

P
Paul Walters
Solid Screwdriver Bits

There honestly isn't too much to say about these, they are good quality bits that do their job well and fit in the LTT Screwdriver. The pre-made packs are affordable and well thought out as is the minimal packaging they come in.

In regards to a storage suggestion though...

It would be interesting if LTT could offer something similar to those "customizable" driver bit trays you see at the hardware store from the likes of DeWalt, Bosch, Milwaukee, etc. They tend to be all a similar generic latching plastic box with "swappable" inserts... but you can't buy the inserts separately! I'd honestly pay for a version that you could customize and upgrade; you could even sell them "pre-loaded" with customer selected bit packs!

Just a thought.

T
Terry Wright

Screwdriver Bit Set

M
Mitchell
So nice I bought it twice!

I enjoyed mine so much that I bought this second one for my dad. Both get used all the time and put my other ratcheting screwdrivers to shame.

Q
Quincy
Decent, but brittle

I ordered all of the bit sets, together with the screwdriver, a few months ago.
All bits look great and look like they're great quality.

However.. This happened to not be the case for me, since I've had to - twice now - request new sets. 1 bit of both the Specialty set and the Torx/Security set bent and broke during use.
I have some experience when it comes to repairing phones, laptops and whatnot, so I know how to handle precision bits. I used to use a cheap set until I decided to treat myself to this LTT merch.

The cheaper bits never even had a scratch, while on 2 separate occasions the LTT bits broke. I hope these incidents were flukes, but I somehow doubt that.

I hope the new sets received (for free, with good and friendly service) prove these to be flukes, since I really like these products.

If so, I will update my review accordingly.

Be cautious.

I bought these for use on electronics and hydraulic gear. They are all sized correctly and the selection is good for general use. The bluing does start wearing off after the first use, but the bits don't seem to be affected.

Good, but not great

Before get into review, Iâ€™d recommend this screwdriver all day ,one, even w/ the minor 2 issues it has.
Hated to delete 2 stars for the following, but have to be fair and as dint have Â½ starsâ€¦.no choice. For comparison, Milwaukee (a fav brand and Klein; had 1 and 0 stars respectively for the ratcheting screwdrivers b/c of slop, storage breakage of Klein, and hardbjt removal on Milwaukee to name just a few that I reviewed after 4 mins this of use)
1) would prefer the silver color for bits just like the silver shaft, as the black is wearing right off and quickly
2) the size/number of bit is pretty much impossible to read w/ the black coating, not to mention, black coating wearing off and makes it harder. If Bit No/size a black 9r same color of the silver shaft, would be so much easier to read; & for those not in construction trades and donâ€™t know bit size by site, Ames it quite difficult to read. So much so, Iâ€™ve got 4 ppl on my crew pulling out cell camera to zoom in to see what bit size they have; especially for the ones not used dailyâ€¦.like specially, torx, hex, Phillips bit sets that can go down to â€œ0-00â€ zies etcâ€¦
Lastly, having the black coating flake off into sensitive electronics can be bad; but Iâ€™ve yet to have had an issue personally from this, and hope never will.
As I like the black, especially when receiving my multiple black shaft â€˜drivers, gonna look pretty awesome! Making my total number of screwdrivers to 5 And total bit packs to 19 total, yep, thatâ€™s right; cuz when in electronics repair and definitely the trades (a sparky, GC, remodeled, & doing a lot of hardware installsâ€¦can wear thru bits quite fast, depending on use case). If the color and stamped â€œbit size/numberâ€ being an issueâ€¦.5/5 all day long, and do like the fit, magnet, & storage in handle more than any of my other 40 screwdrivers. Lastly, the ratchet selector mechanism is actually CORRECT and not backwards from all others, so thx Linus for pushing this feature! Otherwise, balance great, bits so easy to remove/replace in storage handle and use! My fav screwdriver to date and definitely my fav ratcheting screwdriver period! Nothing comes close for price, features, functions, AND USING.
Now Iâ€™m just waiting for that Srubby, and be happy to test for you, cuz having a stubby for hvac/plumbing/electrical, cabinet installsâ€¦.are very valuable, imo.

J
J.W.
Great screwdriver, no torx feels bad

I like the screwdriver a lot, it's exactly as advertised and works great.

However, I feel like torx screws are way more common than square ones, I would have liked to have at least some torx bits included, and it feels like a cheap upsell to not have any in there. Also, two flatheads are too much, you could have easily done no squares, single flathead, and you could add three torx bits, instead we get three (maybe four) useless bits.

Peter Broad
Bits Galore and great service

I purchased the LTT screwdriver; which is amazingly useful; and one of the straight bits was pointed rather than straight. LTT replaced the entire standard set of bits and offered me a second set as well.
I love all the bits and I use the screwdriver around the house all the time. It is my go-to screwdriver. I have all the bit sets now so I am hoping Linus is working on a bit holder.
Great customer support and great product.

There really should be a box to hold these ğŸ˜Š
If one is made available on the store i will update this review to 5 stars (had my brother print a temporary box but he didn't have flexible printing material ğŸ˜‚)

E
E.S.
what am amazing tool!

When you guys announced the driver I was so jazzed to get my hands on it. Watching how much effort went into the design,the materials and testing. If this thing was on the same level as the 3! Dad hats I've purchased over the last 3 years, I knew I was in for a great experience. This driver does not disappoint, love the handle design, big fan of the bit storage, and the ratcheting action and magnet make every job easier! I was an employee of Home Depot for 15 years and in all that time, every driver I've had in hand can't hold a candle to the LTT driver. You all have achieved insane quality without gouging your customers ala Snap-on or other big brands. Only question I have is there would be plans to do a "game bit" for working on Super Nintendo and such?

d
dapperSnowman
Good for more than just computers

This has been on my hip for 40 hours a week at my job ever since I got this screwdriver, and its yet to let me down. The one thing I don't have is a great place to store all the specialty bits I also ordered. I'm not going to be able to keep them in the LTT cardboard forever every time I have to swap out my bit loadouts. I might have to 3D print a holder for all my lesser used security bits.

Felim Clarke
Good... BUT

Bought 2 sets of the Metric Hex Set and 2 sets off the Torx / Security Torx Set. The Torx set is good from what I have used of it so far, so I would recommend them.

The Metric Hex is a different story. While I canâ€™t fault the bits themselves the issue is with myself.

I didnâ€™t read what was actually in the bit set. Whilst you do get 12 bits in the box you actually only get 9 different bits. I stupidly thought I was getting 12 different sized bits because why would you sell a bit set with 3 duplicate bit sizes? If I had off seen that I wouldnâ€™t never have bought them.

Overall - Good... but double check before you buy.

Missing PZ bits

I got the bits with the screwdriver. They're really nice.
However I'm missing pz1 and pz2 bits a lot, since I'm more of a hobbyist than pc builder, and in Europe the PZ bits are more widely used than PH.
Tried to search for them online, impossible to find, so I'll have to buy some regular ones and cut the 5mm off. Tedious :(

J
Jason Bent
JIS Bits?

Hey Linus, you've said on the WAN show several times that you read every review so I figured this may be the best place to make this request. Would you please look into adding JIS (Japanese Industrial Standard) bits to the options for the screwdriver? On all Japanese motorcycles (and presumably cars as well?) the cross head screws and bolts that appear to be phillips are NOT that, but rather they are JIS. They look very similar, but trying to use a standard phillips driver on a JIS fastener very often results in the fastener stripping out and having to then be drilled out. As a mechanic, having the proper tool makes a big difference and I would love to make your already kickass screwdriver an even more versatile tool in my toolbox. I know I may be in the minority as it's mostly tech enthusiasts who are buying this tool, but I've been shilling it to all my fellow mechanics as it is already a well built driver that stands up to real world abuse in a mechanic shop. Thanks for hearing me out and congrats on your much deserved success!

It may be youtuber merch, but the merchandise is quality stuff

I usually do my research after the fact, but in this case I made an exception and bought both the screwdriver and the backpack. Was not disappointed in either! Both, but especially the backpack, far exceed my expectations for "merch". I expected that given how long I've watched LTT, but it is gratifying to know for sure (and show a bit of support for the years of free videos).

R.D.
Needs to be a Bundle with Storage

The bits are fine on their own. My biggest complaint about the LTT Screwdriver is its lack of storage. I want there to be a way to properly store all the bits when not in the handle of the screwdriver. Think something like the bit storage with iFixit kits. There could be one with a slot to set down the driver along with all the bits, or another option would be a small box that just manages all the bits.

Almost tempted to knock it down to two stars because of the bits packaging in general. Iâ€™m glad itâ€™s just a thick card stock kind of stuff, but nearly all of the boxes tore the first time I opened them. The ones that didnâ€™t I had to be super careful not to let them tear, however theyâ€™re all torn now. Bits flying everywhere! Itâ€™s madness I tell you! Madness!

I donâ€™t have a problem with this being the basic option for people who are getting replacements or just want to toss the spares in a drawer. I would just rather have a place for them to all live that wonâ€™t cause them to get mixed up or lost. I realize it would cost more money, but Iâ€™m willing to buy a full set of bits again if it means Iâ€™d get a nice box to store them when theyâ€™re not in the driver.

The bits are bits. They do their job well, theyâ€™d get five stars if there was better storage for them.

Y
Yuri N.
Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder

Still waiting on my screwdriver (ordered bits first), quality seems nice but donâ€™t fit in any of my existing drivers to test properly. Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder. The cardboard box they came in is already torn just from shipping and the bits are just flopping around inside.

It would be nice if there was a screwdriver accessory to hold spare bits, either a dedicated box with little clips to hold them in place. Or, if you wanted to be fancy the holder could be a little pod with the same internals as the screwdriver! I think that would be cool!

D.H.
Love the bits. Hate the holders.

I haven't had a chance to use any yet but the finish is perfect, hollow ground on the flats and no burs to be found.
The packs themselves are very hard to open without tearing the card stock construction, there is nothing retaining the bits inside and WHEN the holder finally tears you'll just have to store them loose or buy and modify a cheap 3rd party holder to fit the smaller bit shanks.

Tip for opening these packs: slide a small blade like a dinner knife or feeler gauge in from the side and twist it back towards the hinge to pry the tab up. It'll help the holder last as long as possible and you're less likely to dump the bits.

Just the tip?

You bet it's just the tip, multiple black ones at that!

Jokes aside, these are very high quality. LTT just needs to make a lil bit case for these short babies, because once you remove a single bit from the original packaging it's like the Berlin wall collapsed with the rest.

R
Richard Lum

always handy to have all the bibs and bobs

M
M.M.
Poor packaging resulted in many missing bits on delivery

Now, I get that we all strive to be "eco" this and "bio" that, but this item is packaged straight-up wrong.
Only 7/12 bits arrived safe, the rest are lost - the bigger box that my shipment arrived in was "sealed", but not "hermetically sealed". Actually, that's another thing... why isn't either of the boxes even properly sealed with scotch tape? How does such a rookie mistake even happen?

Take note: the bits are *only* packaged in a tiny cardboard box. This box is not sealed in any way - no plastic, no glue, no "tiny IKEA-style rubber bit-holding-thingy".
It can just open itself up while in transit - in fact, it seems like a dead certainty.

LTT Guys, I love you, I love your eco-efforts, but at some point reality steps in. If Linus reviewed a competitor and *barely half the bits were even in the box*... well...

C
Cameron

\u003cb class='jdgm-rev__title'\u003eGreat, But No iPhone Standoff Bit.\u003c/b\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eEvery iPhone since the 5 (almost a decade) has used the same standoffs to hold the logic board down.  I purchased four of the screwdrivers with specialty bit addons for the whole team in our repair shop.  My hope was to replace all of the cheap bits/screwdrivers we have in house, especially the y000/0.6 that never seem to fit right.  I thought these would have all the specialty bits I would need for a small repair shop, but as I replaced all the commonly used iFixit bits in my silicone mat with these I realized that the iPhone standoff bit I use almost daily was not a part of the specialty bit set (or any offered here).  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHear my pleas and please offer this as an optional bit in this set or another because I discovered finding a 1/4\" iPhone standoff bit online is basically impossible.  It would have to be custom ordered/made in bulk.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__pics'\u003e  \u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__vids'\u003e   \u003c/div\u003e Love it

The screwdriver is very well made, the tolerances are perfect, the ratchet action is really nice and tight. If Linus reads this review, I would like to suggest that the extra bit sets be sold in a combo pack with a case with an all-black or black and orange option with a black or stainless metal clasp, also put a hole on it that's big enough to put a carabiner through it.

D

The Bit heads are sometimes not large enough

I used all of the extra bit heads that I ordered to build PCs/ 3D printer/cat house/moar stuff. The largest hex bit head was often not big enough besides that one downfall. The bits are durable and I liked them.

Overall I love them and I will be restocking some of the other variants too.

Don't know yet, haven't gotten the screw driver lol

Have all the bits, but waiting for the driver. I'm sure it'll be good with all the care ltt put into it

T
Tim
Great bits, but packaging needs some adjustments.

I bought 9 sets of bits, about 3 of them arrived in tact, 2 were partially in tact, and 4 had come open during shipping and were scattered throughout the package.

Not the worst thing ever, but unfortunately it seems one of those loose bits exfilrated the package during shipping, so one set isn't complete.

I'd like to see some tape or a sticker placed over the bit packet opening to ensure they stay closed until opened with a knife or scissors.

As a secondary product, it'd be great if you stocked a large, labelled bit-holder tray to store all the bits which aren't currently equipped in the screwdriver.

As for the bits themselves, they look excellent.
Great work on the actual product!

A
Anonymous
Scattered Bits, but overall (just) ok

All bits arrived, but they arrived scattered around the main packaging. I appreciate LTT trying to reduce plastic use and keeping packaging somewhat minimal, but they need to figure out something to keep the bits in the package so the bits don't end up scattered around the main package.

Apart from that, my next biggest complaint is some of the bits are very difficult to read the embossed text, and I would have loved for the embossed text to be on all 6 sides. It seems some screws aren't embossed as deeply as others. When loading out the screwdriver, I like to have the embossed text visible so I can better find the bit I am looking for, but some of the bits are really difficult to tell. I group similar bits together so I can use the near by bits to determine what a particular bit is, but would like to not have to.

For Storage, I have the set that came with the screwdriver and 1 other load out. I keep 1 set in the screwdriver and the other bits in the original package and keep the package in the box the Screwdriver shipped in.

All the bits seem very durable, so overall I would rate the bits as just ok.

I
Invvard
Good bits but it lacks a holder

These are good bits (as good as the ones that come with the Screwdriver), the only grief is that it comes in a thin cardboard holder and there is no way it'll hold anything in after a few open/close. Even being cautious opening it for the first time didn't prevent some tear in the cardboard.

I don't think LTT Store could offer a holder for the price, but something should be offered, i.e. a rubber holder along with an optional case that could hold said rubber holders. I'm pretty sure the team is already thinking about something, let's hope it won't take them 3 years to come up with a solution, hahaha

In the mean time, there are some options available on Amazon for example, but they are for standard sized bits. It works but it requires some effort to extract the bits as there is very little going above the edge.

On a final note, I would have appreciated some visual(s) of the packaging.

{"html":"
R
Roar
Needs a case

Maybe I am wrong, maybe I am being too critical, but I am so surprised that these bit sets do not come with a case/holder.

Every bits set I have bought in my entire life came with a case/holder, so I naturally thought it would be the same here.

I am giving it a one star due to feedback and the lack of adjustment in the product page. There should be images of the *actual products*, actual showing that it comes in a cardbox box where the bits are just stacked horisontally next to each other. For me this is close to false advertisement because a lot of people clearly expected more from this product.

I don't care if the product would be a bit more expensive, just give me a friggin' case to store them with. I bought the screwdriver and three additional bits sets in order to be organized when building PCs, but now I have to find a way to organize the stuff so I can avoid losing them. My experience is ruined because it feels cheap. The product is great, but not the whole experience.

J
Jonathan Huff
Great price for a great variety of bits! I love that I can fit all 12 in the LTT screwdriver handle

My only real feedback is that I'd like to have a nice place to store and organize all my bits, since I bought every one of the sets!

J
John Hoffman
Its nearly a replacement for my old iFixit kit

I kind of love these bits. The quality seems excellent, and the variety is equally good. The overall selection is almost a superset of my old iFixit kit.

I even designed and 3d printed a holder for them all. :)

V
Valentin L.
Almost great

I bought each set to go with my LTT screwdriver. I'm happy with them but I have a couple of notes to make it perfect : black is pretty but hard to see the engraved size on it and I know it might be an European thing but why not a Pozidriv set, they are like everywhere here (I have a big ifixit set of bits, they got almost every bits you offer and little more like a complete set of Pozidriv).

For people saying they need a holder, I know you guys are working on it, but I really love Wera design on their â€05136463001 and â€05136459001 products, it's simple and don't feel cheap, I'll use them for now and wait to see what you guys come up with.

N
Noah Wheeler
Bits are fine, lack of holders limits useability

The bits are fine. Not a huge fan of black as it makes it just a little extra difficult in poor lightning to tell which bit is which, but i'll give it a pass because it looks cool. That being said especially with the smaller sizes it becomes hard to tell.
already when putting a bit back into the packaging I can't tell if I've put it in the correct order or not.

What I don't like I really would've expected a little rubber/plastic bit holder or something other than cardboard to keep the bits in place and organized when they aren't in the screwdriver itself. I bought 2 additional bit sets and I don't really want to risk putting them in my tool bag because I know the cardboard is gonna pop out and a million tiny little black bits are going to get lost in the shadows. I'm giving such a harsh hit on the rating just because I believe that these lack of holders are really gonna limit the use I get out of it unless I go out and buy my own additional holder, something that I really shouldn't have to do. I can't remember the last time I bought a set of bits that didn't come with holders.

Finally just a small pet peeve that doesn't really matter because the cardboard packaging isn't going to last anyway is that I don't love that you can't tell what bit you are grabbing out of the box. The icon on the front of box when the flap is open just shows the base style. This means on the torx set 9/12 bits have an identical icon. A little text below each icon with the type of bit like you have on the other side of the flap would've been nice. This is probably a bit pedantic as we've already established the cardboard is going to get trashed anyway.

I'll update the review if I notice any functionality issues with the shorter design but so far seems like there's no major downsides. My primary application is generally automotive and random engineering projects.

T
Teagan Werner

No corners weâ€™re cut. There more than enough to last a long timw

Chris
Torx Set

Bit quality is great.

Would have preferred the Torx set include T27 and T40 (maybe T35) rather than the smaller sizes. Understandable for a tech-focused product, but the smaller end of this set feels more at home in a precision driver kit, not a full size ratcheting driver.

Greatly appreciate the lack of single use plastic in the packaging, but would like to see a cardboard package that at least holds the bits in place. Just some little dividers so they don't float around freely when a couple are removed.

Screwdriver Bit Set

abnewwest
Fine I guess

The non-standard length, well, that's just silly and lacks imagination, kind of like selling bits in only a cardboard box rather than with a clip to hold them.

Torx pack skips size 27 security, one of the most common and no Pozidrive for the Europeans.

M
Matt Finnie
TORX FTW!

I don't know how many times I find I need a TORX bit for something and can't seem to ever find the right one. There are 12 of them in the TORX set ranging from T3 to T30! I shouldn't have any trouble getting the right one now and is a must in my toolbox. Combined with all the bits that come with the screwdriver I have a lot of great options should I need them. The only downside I see is that the bits come in a cardboard box so it's kind of useless to store them in it. I would have loved to have the option to buy a durable bit storage box to keep them in, and I may have even picked up some additional bit packages just in case. Overall great product and has a nice range of available bits, but the storage options could have been better.

Buy multiples and safe yourself time

I purchased 1 of EACH bit set. Save yourself some time and just buy 1 of each NOW. FYI, when you buy these, go ahead and magnetic or rubberized bit holders on Amazon. The screwdriver comes with the "Standard" bit set but I would recommend buying a backup set as well.

G
G.R.
good but not great IMO (Metric set review)

So I use a lot of the H2 (2mm) and H2.5 (2.5mm) for RC race cars and the bits are way too loose for me. I use MIP tools for RC and they are amazing, but uncomfortable, so when I bought the LTT screwdriver I was excited that it came with 2 and 2.5mm hex bits because I didn't doubt my boi Linus about the comfort. Unfortunately the Hexes are loose and the 2mm actually measured 1.95mm on my calipers and that is bad when it comes to small screws that need to be tight for competitive RC racing. the 2.5mm bit was 2.47 and 3mm was spot on and felt great. MIP tools use a flat sharp tip and these are more soft and rounded. Wouldn't recommend these if you need to remove some screws that have Loctite on them. screwdriver is amazing though. My boi Linus didn't lie when he said "trust me bro"

S
Stephen
Disappointing packaging

Love the screwdriver and the bits themselves are good. I bought 3 additional bit sets with my screwdriver and 2/3 of them were opened and the bits scattered through the shipping box rattling around loose. For how much Linus focuses on packaging of products he reviews I expected a lot more there tbh.

J
Joshua
All the bits...

I ended up buying all of the available bit packages, except for the standard bit set since th at already came with the screwdriver.

The bits seem good for the most part, though I do find some of the markings hard to read and a couple just don't seem to be there at all.

I would really love to have a labelled case for bit storage. While the box they come in has a nice presentation, it isn't really suitable for long term storage and doesn't hold the bits in place.

I have looked at generic options, but they generally aren't labelled and since these bits are a bit shorter than normal, they would be challenging to use. In the case of some magnetic options, they would go too far into the holder and be hard to identify / remove from the holder. In the more standard rubber strip designs, you I find they get inserted too far and have I have to use another bit to get the bit out.

Quality steel

These bits and the whole screwdriver system in a whole are superior products.

J
Julius Martin
Great product, missing opportunities

I love the screw driver! It actuallu makes the tedious task of driving screws kind of fun. I've bought along with the standard screwdriver and heads, a few extra bit sets.

After this purchase, I realized that I had no where to put the bits. An intuitive bit holder for LTT bits would be an awesome side product!

Another issue I faced was the length of the drivers are quite short. This makes it hard to reach screws in electronics that are enclosed deep within the mechanism. An extension piece for the screwdriver would make this product absolutely perfect!

All that said, this is the best screwdriver I've ever used.

Love the bit selection super useful for my computer builds and house fixin!

General screwdriver use

The bits work well enough, I wish they sold all the bits together for a dollar off or something in that nature. As I bought all of them.

I had to find JIS bits for use on my Honda/Subaru on McMaster. Perhaps something that Linus can add.

P
Paul Walters
Solid Screwdriver Bits

There honestly isn't too much to say about these, they are good quality bits that do their job well and fit in the LTT Screwdriver. The pre-made packs are affordable and well thought out as is the minimal packaging they come in.

In regards to a storage suggestion though...

It would be interesting if LTT could offer something similar to those "customizable" driver bit trays you see at the hardware store from the likes of DeWalt, Bosch, Milwaukee, etc. They tend to be all a similar generic latching plastic box with "swappable" inserts... but you can't buy the inserts separately! I'd honestly pay for a version that you could customize and upgrade; you could even sell them "pre-loaded" with customer selected bit packs!

Just a thought.

T
Terry Wright

Screwdriver Bit Set

M
Mitchell
So nice I bought it twice!

I enjoyed mine so much that I bought this second one for my dad. Both get used all the time and put my other ratcheting screwdrivers to shame.

Q
Quincy
Decent, but brittle

I ordered all of the bit sets, together with the screwdriver, a few months ago.
All bits look great and look like they're great quality.

However.. This happened to not be the case for me, since I've had to - twice now - request new sets. 1 bit of both the Specialty set and the Torx/Security set bent and broke during use.
I have some experience when it comes to repairing phones, laptops and whatnot, so I know how to handle precision bits. I used to use a cheap set until I decided to treat myself to this LTT merch.

The cheaper bits never even had a scratch, while on 2 separate occasions the LTT bits broke. I hope these incidents were flukes, but I somehow doubt that.

I hope the new sets received (for free, with good and friendly service) prove these to be flukes, since I really like these products.

If so, I will update my review accordingly.

Be cautious.

I bought these for use on electronics and hydraulic gear. They are all sized correctly and the selection is good for general use. The bluing does start wearing off after the first use, but the bits don't seem to be affected.

Good, but not great

Before get into review, Iâ€™d recommend this screwdriver all day ,one, even w/ the minor 2 issues it has.
Hated to delete 2 stars for the following, but have to be fair and as dint have Â½ starsâ€¦.no choice. For comparison, Milwaukee (a fav brand and Klein; had 1 and 0 stars respectively for the ratcheting screwdrivers b/c of slop, storage breakage of Klein, and hardbjt removal on Milwaukee to name just a few that I reviewed after 4 mins this of use)
1) would prefer the silver color for bits just like the silver shaft, as the black is wearing right off and quickly
2) the size/number of bit is pretty much impossible to read w/ the black coating, not to mention, black coating wearing off and makes it harder. If Bit No/size a black 9r same color of the silver shaft, would be so much easier to read; & for those not in construction trades and donâ€™t know bit size by site, Ames it quite difficult to read. So much so, Iâ€™ve got 4 ppl on my crew pulling out cell camera to zoom in to see what bit size they have; especially for the ones not used dailyâ€¦.like specially, torx, hex, Phillips bit sets that can go down to â€œ0-00â€ zies etcâ€¦
Lastly, having the black coating flake off into sensitive electronics can be bad; but Iâ€™ve yet to have had an issue personally from this, and hope never will.
As I like the black, especially when receiving my multiple black shaft â€˜drivers, gonna look pretty awesome! Making my total number of screwdrivers to 5 And total bit packs to 19 total, yep, thatâ€™s right; cuz when in electronics repair and definitely the trades (a sparky, GC, remodeled, & doing a lot of hardware installsâ€¦can wear thru bits quite fast, depending on use case). If the color and stamped â€œbit size/numberâ€ being an issueâ€¦.5/5 all day long, and do like the fit, magnet, & storage in handle more than any of my other 40 screwdrivers. Lastly, the ratchet selector mechanism is actually CORRECT and not backwards from all others, so thx Linus for pushing this feature! Otherwise, balance great, bits so easy to remove/replace in storage handle and use! My fav screwdriver to date and definitely my fav ratcheting screwdriver period! Nothing comes close for price, features, functions, AND USING.
Now Iâ€™m just waiting for that Srubby, and be happy to test for you, cuz having a stubby for hvac/plumbing/electrical, cabinet installsâ€¦.are very valuable, imo.

J
J.W.
Great screwdriver, no torx feels bad

I like the screwdriver a lot, it's exactly as advertised and works great.

However, I feel like torx screws are way more common than square ones, I would have liked to have at least some torx bits included, and it feels like a cheap upsell to not have any in there. Also, two flatheads are too much, you could have easily done no squares, single flathead, and you could add three torx bits, instead we get three (maybe four) useless bits.

Peter Broad
Bits Galore and great service

I purchased the LTT screwdriver; which is amazingly useful; and one of the straight bits was pointed rather than straight. LTT replaced the entire standard set of bits and offered me a second set as well.
I love all the bits and I use the screwdriver around the house all the time. It is my go-to screwdriver. I have all the bit sets now so I am hoping Linus is working on a bit holder.
Great customer support and great product.

Needs a better case

There really should be a box to hold these ğŸ˜Š
If one is made available on the store i will update this review to 5 stars (had my brother print a temporary box but he didn't have flexible printing material ğŸ˜‚)

E
E.S.
what am amazing tool!

When you guys announced the driver I was so jazzed to get my hands on it. Watching how much effort went into the design,the materials and testing. If this thing was on the same level as the 3! Dad hats I've purchased over the last 3 years, I knew I was in for a great experience. This driver does not disappoint, love the handle design, big fan of the bit storage, and the ratcheting action and magnet make every job easier! I was an employee of Home Depot for 15 years and in all that time, every driver I've had in hand can't hold a candle to the LTT driver. You all have achieved insane quality without gouging your customers ala Snap-on or other big brands. Only question I have is there would be plans to do a "game bit" for working on Super Nintendo and such?

d
dapperSnowman
Good for more than just computers

This has been on my hip for 40 hours a week at my job ever since I got this screwdriver, and its yet to let me down. The one thing I don't have is a great place to store all the specialty bits I also ordered. I'm not going to be able to keep them in the LTT cardboard forever every time I have to swap out my bit loadouts. I might have to 3D print a holder for all my lesser used security bits.

F
Felim Clarke
Good... BUT

Bought 2 sets of the Metric Hex Set and 2 sets off the Torx / Security Torx Set. The Torx set is good from what I have used of it so far, so I would recommend them.

The Metric Hex is a different story. While I canâ€™t fault the bits themselves the issue is with myself.

I didnâ€™t read what was actually in the bit set. Whilst you do get 12 bits in the box you actually only get 9 different bits. I stupidly thought I was getting 12 different sized bits because why would you sell a bit set with 3 duplicate bit sizes? If I had off seen that I wouldnâ€™t never have bought them.

Overall - Good... but double check before you buy.

Missing PZ bits

I got the bits with the screwdriver. They're really nice.
However I'm missing pz1 and pz2 bits a lot, since I'm more of a hobbyist than pc builder, and in Europe the PZ bits are more widely used than PH.
Tried to search for them online, impossible to find, so I'll have to buy some regular ones and cut the 5mm off. Tedious :(

J
Jason Bent
JIS Bits?

Hey Linus, you've said on the WAN show several times that you read every review so I figured this may be the best place to make this request. Would you please look into adding JIS (Japanese Industrial Standard) bits to the options for the screwdriver? On all Japanese motorcycles (and presumably cars as well?) the cross head screws and bolts that appear to be phillips are NOT that, but rather they are JIS. They look very similar, but trying to use a standard phillips driver on a JIS fastener very often results in the fastener stripping out and having to then be drilled out. As a mechanic, having the proper tool makes a big difference and I would love to make your already kickass screwdriver an even more versatile tool in my toolbox. I know I may be in the minority as it's mostly tech enthusiasts who are buying this tool, but I've been shilling it to all my fellow mechanics as it is already a well built driver that stands up to real world abuse in a mechanic shop. Thanks for hearing me out and congrats on your much deserved success!

It may be youtuber merch, but the merchandise is quality stuff

I usually do my research after the fact, but in this case I made an exception and bought both the screwdriver and the backpack. Was not disappointed in either! Both, but especially the backpack, far exceed my expectations for "merch". I expected that given how long I've watched LTT, but it is gratifying to know for sure (and show a bit of support for the years of free videos).

R
R.D.
Needs to be a Bundle with Storage

The bits are fine on their own. My biggest complaint about the LTT Screwdriver is its lack of storage. I want there to be a way to properly store all the bits when not in the handle of the screwdriver. Think something like the bit storage with iFixit kits. There could be one with a slot to set down the driver along with all the bits, or another option would be a small box that just manages all the bits.

Almost tempted to knock it down to two stars because of the bits packaging in general. Iâ€™m glad itâ€™s just a thick card stock kind of stuff, but nearly all of the boxes tore the first time I opened them. The ones that didnâ€™t I had to be super careful not to let them tear, however theyâ€™re all torn now. Bits flying everywhere! Itâ€™s madness I tell you! Madness!

I donâ€™t have a problem with this being the basic option for people who are getting replacements or just want to toss the spares in a drawer. I would just rather have a place for them to all live that wonâ€™t cause them to get mixed up or lost. I realize it would cost more money, but Iâ€™m willing to buy a full set of bits again if it means Iâ€™d get a nice box to store them when theyâ€™re not in the driver.

The bits are bits. They do their job well, theyâ€™d get five stars if there was better storage for them.

Y
Yuri N.
Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder

Still waiting on my screwdriver (ordered bits first), quality seems nice but donâ€™t fit in any of my existing drivers to test properly. Desperately needs a dedicated bit holder. The cardboard box they came in is already torn just from shipping and the bits are just flopping around inside.

It would be nice if there was a screwdriver accessory to hold spare bits, either a dedicated box with little clips to hold them in place. Or, if you wanted to be fancy the holder could be a little pod with the same internals as the screwdriver! I think that would be cool!

D.H.
Love the bits. Hate the holders.

I haven't had a chance to use any yet but the finish is perfect, hollow ground on the flats and no burs to be found.
The packs themselves are very hard to open without tearing the card stock construction, there is nothing retaining the bits inside and WHEN the holder finally tears you'll just have to store them loose or buy and modify a cheap 3rd party holder to fit the smaller bit shanks.

Tip for opening these packs: slide a small blade like a dinner knife or feeler gauge in from the side and twist it back towards the hinge to pry the tab up. It'll help the holder last as long as possible and you're less likely to dump the bits.

Just the tip?

You bet it's just the tip, multiple black ones at that!

Jokes aside, these are very high quality. LTT just needs to make a lil bit case for these short babies, because once you remove a single bit from the original packaging it's like the Berlin wall collapsed with the rest.

R
Richard Lum

always handy to have all the bibs and bobs

M
M.M.
Poor packaging resulted in many missing bits on delivery

Now, I get that we all strive to be "eco" this and "bio" that, but this item is packaged straight-up wrong.
Only 7/12 bits arrived safe, the rest are lost - the bigger box that my shipment arrived in was "sealed", but not "hermetically sealed". Actually, that's another thing... why isn't either of the boxes even properly sealed with scotch tape? How does such a rookie mistake even happen?

Take note: the bits are *only* packaged in a tiny cardboard box. This box is not sealed in any way - no plastic, no glue, no "tiny IKEA-style rubber bit-holding-thingy".
It can just open itself up while in transit - in fact, it seems like a dead certainty.

LTT Guys, I love you, I love your eco-efforts, but at some point reality steps in. If Linus reviewed a competitor and *barely half the bits were even in the box*... well...

C
Cameron

\u003cb class='jdgm-rev__title'\u003eGreat, But No iPhone Standoff Bit.\u003c/b\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eEvery iPhone since the 5 (almost a decade) has used the same standoffs to hold the logic board down.  I purchased four of the screwdrivers with specialty bit addons for the whole team in our repair shop.  My hope was to replace all of the cheap bits/screwdrivers we have in house, especially the y000/0.6 that never seem to fit right.  I thought these would have all the specialty bits I would need for a small repair shop, but as I replaced all the commonly used iFixit bits in my silicone mat with these I realized that the iPhone standoff bit I use almost daily was not a part of the specialty bit set (or any offered here).  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHear my pleas and please offer this as an optional bit in this set or another because I discovered finding a 1/4\" iPhone standoff bit online is basically impossible.  It would have to be custom ordered/made in bulk.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__pics'\u003e  \u003c/div\u003e \u003cdiv class='jdgm-rev__vids'\u003e   \u003c/div\u003e class='jdgm-rev__body'\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe bits seem well made, and the material seems good. My only complaint is just that there isn't a great storage option for additional bits. Since they're shorter than usual 1/4\" bits they don't fit super well into either of the 1/4\" bit holders I've got. Each set comes in small paper boxes, which is good for sustainability, but not great for long term storage of the extra bits. T
Tim
Great bits, but packaging needs some adjustments.

I bought 9 sets of bits, about 3 of them arrived in tact, 2 were partially in tact, and 4 had come open during shipping and were scattered throughout the package.

Not the worst thing ever, but unfortunately it seems one of those loose bits exfilrated the package during shipping, so one set isn't complete.

I'd like to see some tape or a sticker placed over the bit packet opening to ensure they stay closed until opened with a knife or scissors.

As a secondary product, it'd be great if you stocked a large, labelled bit-holder tray to store all the bits which aren't currently equipped in the screwdriver.

As for the bits themselves, they look excellent.
Great work on the actual product!

A
Anonymous
Scattered Bits, but overall (just) ok

All bits arrived, but they arrived scattered around the main packaging. I appreciate LTT trying to reduce plastic use and keeping packaging somewhat minimal, but they need to figure out something to keep the bits in the package so the bits don't end up scattered around the main package.

Apart from that, my next biggest complaint is some of the bits are very difficult to read the embossed text, and I would have loved for the embossed text to be on all 6 sides. It seems some screws aren't embossed as deeply as others. When loading out the screwdriver, I like to have the embossed text visible so I can better find the bit I am looking for, but some of the bits are really difficult to tell. I group similar bits together so I can use the near by bits to determine what a particular bit is, but would like to not have to.

For Storage, I have the set that came with the screwdriver and 1 other load out. I keep 1 set in the screwdriver and the other bits in the original package and keep the package in the box the Screwdriver shipped in.

All the bits seem very durable, so overall I would rate the bits as just ok.

I
Invvard
Good bits but it lacks a holder

These are good bits (as good as the ones that come with the Screwdriver), the only grief is that it comes in a thin cardboard holder and there is no way it'll hold anything in after a few open/close. Even being cautious opening it for the first time didn't prevent some tear in the cardboard.

I don't think LTT Store could offer a holder for the price, but something should be offered, i.e. a rubber holder along with an optional case that could hold said rubber holders. I'm pretty sure the team is already thinking about something, let's hope it won't take them 3 years to come up with a solution, hahaha

In the mean time, there are some options available on Amazon for example, but they are for standard sized bits. It works but it requires some effort to extract the bits as there is very little going above the edge.

On a final note, I would have appreciated some visual(s) of the packaging.

R
Roar
Needs a case

Maybe I am wrong, maybe I am being too critical, but I am so surprised that these bit sets do not come with a case/holder.

Every bits set I have bought in my entire life came with a case/holder, so I naturally thought it would be the same here.

I am giving it a one star due to feedback and the lack of adjustment in the product page. There should be images of the *actual products*, actual showing that it comes in a cardbox box where the bits are just stacked horisontally next to each other. For me this is close to false advertisement because a lot of people clearly expected more from this product.

I don't care if the product would be a bit more expensive, just give me a friggin' case to store them with. I bought the screwdriver and three additional bits sets in order to be organized when building PCs, but now I have to find a way to organize the stuff so I can avoid losing them. My experience is ruined because it feels cheap. The product is great, but not the whole experience.

J
Jonathan Huff
Great price for a great variety of bits! I love that I can fit all 12 in the LTT screwdriver handle

My only real feedback is that I'd like to have a nice place to store and organize all my bits, since I bought every one of the sets!

J
John Hoffman
Its nearly a replacement for my old iFixit kit

I kind of love these bits. The quality seems excellent, and the variety is equally good. The overall selection is almost a superset of my old iFixit kit.

I even designed and 3d printed a holder for them all. :)

V
Valentin L.
Almost great

I bought each set to go with my LTT screwdriver. I'm happy with them but I have a couple of notes to make it perfect : black is pretty but hard to see the engraved size on it and I know it might be an European thing but why not a Pozidriv set, they are like everywhere here (I have a big ifixit set of bits, they got almost every bits you offer and little more like a complete set of Pozidriv).

For people saying they need a holder, I know you guys are working on it, but I really love Wera design on their â€05136463001 and â€05136459001 products, it's simple and don't feel cheap, I'll use them for now and wait to see what you guys come up with.

N
Noah Wheeler
Bits are fine, lack of holders limits useability

The bits are fine. Not a huge fan of black as it makes it just a little extra difficult in poor lightning to tell which bit is which, but i'll give it a pass because it looks cool. That being said especially with the smaller sizes it becomes hard to tell.
already when putting a bit back into the packaging I can't tell if I've put it in the correct order or not.

What I don't like I really would've expected a little rubber/plastic bit holder or something other than cardboard to keep the bits in place and organized when they aren't in the screwdriver itself. I bought 2 additional bit sets and I don't really want to risk putting them in my tool bag because I know the cardboard is gonna pop out and a million tiny little black bits are going to get lost in the shadows. I'm giving such a harsh hit on the rating just because I believe that these lack of holders are really gonna limit the use I get out of it unless I go out and buy my own additional holder, something that I really shouldn't have to do. I can't remember the last time I bought a set of bits that didn't come with holders.

Finally just a small pet peeve that doesn't really matter because the cardboard packaging isn't going to last anyway is that I don't love that you can't tell what bit you are grabbing out of the box. The icon on the front of box when the flap is open just shows the base style. This means on the torx set 9/12 bits have an identical icon. A little text below each icon with the type of bit like you have on the other side of the flap would've been nice. This is probably a bit pedantic as we've already established the cardboard is going to get trashed anyway.

I'll update the review if I notice any functionality issues with the shorter design but so far seems like there's no major downsides. My primary application is generally automotive and random engineering projects.

T
Teagan Werner
